The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to matroids, which are a fundamental concept in discrete mathematics and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization problems, which suggests categories such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper applies the problem to social network analysis, which could fall under categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
